--- In junit@yahoogroups.com, &quot;David Jackman&quot; &lt;david.jackman@f...&gt; wrote:
&gt; It&#39;s the same as testing any other method.  Set up the test, call the
&gt; method, then verify the output.
&gt;  
&gt; For example:
&gt;  
&gt; public void testMain()
&gt; {
&gt;     //  Set up the input and output streams
&gt;     System.in = new ByteArrayInputStream(&quot;1&#92;n&quot;.getBytes());
&gt;     ByteArrayOutputStream output = ByteArrayOutputStream();
&gt;     System.out = new PrintStream(output);
&gt;     //  Call the main method
&gt;     MyClass.main(new String[] {});
&gt;     //  Verify the output
&gt;     assertEquals(&quot;You typed a 1.&quot;, output.toString());
&gt; }
&gt;  
&gt; 
